Chilean Stocks: Corpbanca, Endesa, and Empresas La Polar

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-30T20:51:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/chilean-stocks-corpbanca-endesa-and-empresas-la-polar.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:13 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.1 percent to 4,845.32.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)   fell 1.2 percent to 7.6 pesos, the
biggest fall in four weeks. Chile’s sixth-largest lender by
assets began today a preferential rights option period for
shareholders to buy 25.5 billion new shares at a rate of 0.112
for every one they currently own, according to a statement
posted on the website of the Santiago stock exchange. The
preferential rights period will end July 2.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 3.1 percent to
2,514.7 pesos, its lowest price in nine weeks. The Chilean
department store chain announced May 27 it plans to sell as much
as $400 million in new shares to fund expansion plans and shore
up its finances. Shareholders will vote on the plan June 22.  Empresa Nacional de Electricidad SA (ENDESA CC),  Chile ’s
laregst power generator, rose 0.8 percent to 858.61 pesos, the
steepest gain in three weeks. Power generation in Chile grew 7.4
percent in April from a year earlier, according to a statement
posted on the website of Chile’s national statistics institute
INE.  To contact the reporter on this story:
